    public interface PsiPolyVariantReference
extends PsiReference
    Inherit this interface if you want the reference to resolve to more than one element, or if you want to provide resolve result(s) for a superset of valid resolve cases. e.g. in Java references in static context are resolved to non-static methods in case there is no valid candidate. isValidResult() in this case should return false for later analysis by highlighting pass.
    See Also:
    PsiPolyVariantReferenceBase
